Both deliverables are emitted in the bundle directory.

**Key finding:** `feature_008` is a candidate treatment (40% prevalence, +20 pp main response benefit). Its effect is concentrated almost entirely in the 31.4% of patients who simultaneously have `feature_013=0` AND `feature_015=0` AND `feature_021=0` AND `feature_027=0` — within that subgroup, response rate is 79.8% on treatment vs 17.2% off (+62.6 pp, OR 18.98). Outside the subgroup, the treatment effect collapses to +0.8 pp. The four modifiers are independent of each other (phi ≤ 0.004) and each independently neutralizes the treatment effect; treatment assignment is balanced across the subgroup (40.3% vs 40.1%), ruling out confounding by indication. A within-subgroup screen of the remaining 26 features finds no further robust modifier.
